    "body": "<!-- Thank you for your contribution! We appreciate it. The following guidelines will help improve your pull request and facilitate feedback. If anything is unclear, don't hesitate to submit your pull request and ask the maintainers for assistance. -->\r\n\r\n## Motivation\r\nTo align with community model config standard, `modelopt` now exports quantization config in `config.json`, while for legacy reasons, we also keep `hf_quant_config.json`. This PR is to handle two different config formats:\r\n-        hf_quant_config.json format: {\"quantization\": {\"quant_algo\": \"NVFP4\", ...}}\r\n-        config.json quantization_config format: {\"quant_algo\": \"NVFP4\", ...}\r\n\r\nIn future modelopt will deprecate `hf_quant_config.json`, and only keep `config.json`.\r\n\r\n\r\n## Modifications\r\n\r\nModify `ModelOptFp8Config` and `ModelOptFp4Config`. Format handling priority:\r\n\r\n- First: Handle flat format (config.json) - preferred\r\n- Fallback: Handle nested format (hf_quant_config.json) - legacy\r\n\r\n\r\n## Accuracy Test\r\nTesting script:\r\n\r\n```\r\nimport sglang as sgl\r\n\r\ndef main():\r\n    prompts = [\r\n        \"Hello, my name is\",\r\n        \"The president of the United States is\",\r\n        \"The capital of France is\",\r\n        \"The future of AI is\",\r\n    ]\r\n    sampling_params = {\r\n        \"temperature\": 0.01,\r\n        \"top_p\": 0.95,\r\n        \"max_new_tokens\": 20, \r\n        \"stop\": [\"\\n\", \".\", \"!\", \"?\"], \r\n        \"skip_special_tokens\": True\r\n    }\r\n    llm = sgl.Engine(model_path=\"/home/zhiyuc/test_ckpts/TinyLlama-1.1B-Chat-v1.0-fp8\", quantization=\"modelopt\", context_length=1024)\r\n\r\n    outputs = llm.generate(prompts, sampling_params)\r\n    for prompt, output in zip(prompts, outputs):\r\n        print(\"===============================\")\r\n        print(f\"Prompt: {prompt}\")\r\n        print(f\"Generated text: '{output['text']}'\")\r\n        print(f\"Generated text length: {len(output['text'])}\")\r\n        print(f\"Generated text bytes: {output['text'].encode('utf-8', errors='replace')}\")\r\n        if 'meta_info' in output:\r\n            print(f\"Meta info: {output['meta_info']}\")\r\n        print()\r\n\r\nif __name__ == \"__main__\":\r\n    main()\r\n```\r\n`/home/zhiyuc/test_ckpts/TinyLlama-1.1B-Chat-v1.0-fp8` is a local test checkpoint that is quantized by the latest modelopt. The quant config in `config.json` is shown below:\r\n\r\n```\r\n    \"quantization_config\": {\r\n        \"config_groups\": {\r\n            \"group_0\": {\r\n                \"input_activations\": {\r\n                    \"dynamic\": false,\r\n                    \"num_bits\": 8,\r\n                    \"type\": \"float\"\r\n                },\r\n                \"weights\": {\r\n                    \"dynamic\": false,\r\n                    \"num_bits\": 8,\r\n                    \"type\": \"float\"\r\n                },\r\n                \"targets\": [\r\n                    \"Linear\"\r\n                ]\r\n            }\r\n        },\r\n        \"ignore\": [\r\n            \"lm_head\"\r\n        ],\r\n        \"quant_algo\": \"FP8\",\r\n        \"kv_cache_scheme\": {\r\n            \"dynamic\": false,\r\n            \"num_bits\": 8,\r\n            \"type\": \"float\"\r\n        },\r\n        \"producer\": {\r\n            \"name\": \"modelopt\",\r\n            \"version\": \"0.35.0\"\r\n        },\r\n        \"quant_method\": \"modelopt\"\r\n    }\r\n\r\n```\r\n\r\n## Benchmark & Profiling\r\n\r\n<!-- If this PR is expected to impact performance, please provide benchmark and profiling results. Ref: https://docs.sglang.ai/references/benchmark_and_profiling.html -->\r\n\r\n## Checklist\r\n\r\n- [x] Format your code according to the [Code Formatting with Pre-Commit](https://docs.sglang.ai/references/contribution_guide.html#code-formatting-with-pre-commit).\r\n- [ ] Add unit tests as outlined in the [Running Unit Tests](https://docs.sglang.ai/references/contribution_guide.html#running-unit-tests-adding-to-ci).\r\n- [ ] Update documentation / docstrings / example tutorials as needed, according to [Writing Documentation](https://docs.sglang.ai/references/contribution_guide.html#writing-documentation-running-docs-ci).\r\n- [ ] Provide throughput / latency benchmark results and accuracy evaluation results as needed, according to [Benchmark and Profiling](https://docs.sglang.ai/references/benchmark_and_profiling.html) and [Accuracy Results](https://docs.sglang.ai/references/accuracy_evaluation.html).\r\n- [ ] For reviewers: If you haven't made any contributions to this PR and are only assisting with merging the main branch, please remove yourself as a co-author when merging the PR.\r\n- [ ] Please feel free to join our Slack channel at https://slack.sglang.ai to discuss your PR.\r\n",
